snippet.title: 1. Body Dysmorphia: Creating a Healthy Relationship with Food, Chef Amber Caudle
snippet.description:
Food is one of the most abused substances for unhealthy self-soothing. Creating and sustaining a healthy relationship with food involves healing emotional wounds. Watch how one woman recognized her addiction, got to its source and then used food to heal.

▬ Contents of this video  ▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬

00:00 - Intro
00:44 - Body Dysmorphia and dieting
02:28 - Sugar addiction and self-soothing
03:35 - Passion for cooking
04:39 - The messy, healing journey
05:51 - Dealing with health problems
07:08 - Self-love: healing the body with food

▬ About Dr. Nadine Macaluso  ▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬▬

Dr. Nadine Macaluso is a psychologist and licensed marriage and family therapist in private practice. She received her master’s in Counseling Psychology and doctorate in Depth Psychology with an emphasis on Somatic Psychotherapy from Pacifica Graduate Institute in California. Her personal and clinical expertise is in attachment trauma, shame, somatic psychotherapy and relationships. Dr. Nae is also the ex-wife to the infamous Wolf of Wall Street, Jordan Belfort, with whom she shares two beautiful children, Carter and Chandler. Nadine has been happily remarried for 20 years; she and her husband John share a blended family of five children and two dogs, splitting their time between New York and Florida.
